────────────────────────────────────────
RED MATRIX OVERLAY CONTRACT
────────────────────────────────────────

The matrix effect must be red, not green.

The matrix effect is not part of the WhekeOS frame.
It is a separate overlay layer with its own bounds, its own cleanup, and no global clear authority.

Layer model:

Layer 0: terminal background and global clear
Layer 1: main boot animation / logo / loader
Layer 2: log output
Layer 3: red right-side matrix overlay

Layer 3 must be isolated.

The red matrix overlay must:
- draw only inside reserved right-side columns
- use no more than three vertical streams
- not write into logo/header frame space
- not write into log output rows
- not call global clear
- not call mdi_clear
- not call tput clear
- not print '\033[2J'
- not reset the whole terminal
- clean only its own reserved columns
- be disabled automatically on terminals too small to safely reserve the layer
- stop before Stage 4 Interface Handoff

Matrix colours:

MATRIX_RED="$(printf '\033[38;5;196m')"
MATRIX_DARKRED="$(printf '\033[38;5;88m')"
MATRIX_DIMRED="$(printf '\033[38;5;52m')"
MATRIX_AMBER="$(printf '\033[38;5;214m')"
MATRIX_RST="$(printf '\033[0m')"

Required matrix layer helpers:

mdi_matrix_bounds() {
  COLS="$(mdi_term_cols)"
  ROWS="$(mdi_term_rows)"

  [ "$COLS" -lt 90 ] && return 1
  [ "$ROWS" -lt 22 ] && return 1

  MATRIX_COL_1=$((COLS - 10))
  MATRIX_COL_2=$((COLS - 7))
  MATRIX_COL_3=$((COLS - 4))
  MATRIX_ROW_START=2
  MATRIX_ROW_END=$((ROWS - 3))

  return 0
}

mdi_matrix_clear_layer() {
  mdi_matrix_bounds || return 0

  row="$MATRIX_ROW_START"
  while [ "$row" -le "$MATRIX_ROW_END" ]; do
    mdi_move "$row" "$MATRIX_COL_1"; printf ' '
    mdi_move "$row" "$MATRIX_COL_2"; printf ' '
    mdi_move "$row" "$MATRIX_COL_3"; printf ' '
    row=$((row + 1))
  done
}

Required matrix effect:

mdi_fx_matrix_sidefall() {
  mdi_matrix_bounds || return 0

  CHARS='0123456789ABCDEFGHIJKLMNOPQRSTUVWXYZ@#$%*+=-'
  LEN=44
  frame=1

  while [ "$frame" -le 16 ]; do
    row="$MATRIX_ROW_START"

    while [ "$row" -le "$MATRIX_ROW_END" ]; do
      i1=$(( (frame + row) % LEN + 1 ))
      i2=$(( (frame + row + 9) % LEN + 1 ))
      i3=$(( (frame + row + 17) % LEN + 1 ))

      c1="$(printf '%s' "$CHARS" | cut -c "$i1")"
      c2="$(printf '%s' "$CHARS" | cut -c "$i2")"
      c3="$(printf '%s' "$CHARS" | cut -c "$i3")"

      mdi_move "$row" "$MATRIX_COL_1"
      printf '%b%s%b' "$MATRIX_DIMRED" "$c1" "$MATRIX_RST"

      if [ "$row" -gt "$((MATRIX_ROW_START + 2))" ]; then
        mdi_move "$row" "$MATRIX_COL_2"
        printf '%b%s%b' "$MATRIX_RED" "$c2" "$MATRIX_RST"
      fi

      if [ "$row" -gt "$((MATRIX_ROW_START + 5))" ]; then
        mdi_move "$row" "$MATRIX_COL_3"
        printf '%b%s%b' "$MATRIX_DARKRED" "$c3" "$MATRIX_RST"
      fi

      row=$((row + 1))
    done

    sleep 0.05

    # Clear only the matrix layer. Never clear the whole terminal here.
    mdi_matrix_clear_layer

    frame=$((frame + 1))
  done

  mdi_matrix_clear_layer
}

